message: Harry & Kate Freeman were not slaves but indentured servants who worked to pay off their passage to America from England that was paid by J.L. Hardenbergh. Once their debt was paid off they acquired land in Auburn and created an established African American community within Auburn and the Freemans worked closely alongside Harriet Tubman on the underground railroad.
